BECAUSE SHE HATES ME.

465
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:28,291
- Mizuki: THAT'S NOT
TRUE AT ALL.

466
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:31,208
YOSHII, YOUR SISTER LOVES YOU.
IT'S PRETTY OBVIOUS.

467
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:33,958
- SO SHE REALLY DOES THINK
I'M STUPIDEST.

468
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:36,291
- DON'T BE SILLY. HER ONLY
REASON FOR BEING HERE IS

469
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:37,750
TO MAKE SURE
YOU'RE OKAY,

470
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:41,333
WHICH JUST GOES TO SHOW
HOW MUCH SHE CARES ABOUT YOU.

471
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:44,041
- SHE TRAVELED ALL THE WAY HERE
FROM AMERICA FOR YOU.

472
00:19:44,125 --> 00:19:46,000
DIDN'T HAVE ANY OTHER
REASON, DID SHE?

473
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,666
- Akihisa: MAYBE THEY'RE RIGHT
ABOUT MY SISTER.

474
00:19:52,583 --> 00:19:55,000
WHAT SHOULD I MAKE
FOR DINNER?

475
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:57,708
SHE HASN'T BEEN BACK
HOME FOR AWHILE NOW.

476
00:19:57,791 --> 00:20:01,875
I KNOW WHAT I'LL COOK.
JAPANESE FOOD.

477
00:20:01,958 --> 00:20:04,000
I'M HOME, PLEASE TELL ME
YOU HAVE CLOTHES ON.

478
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:06,500
- VERY FUNNY.
HOW WAS YOUR DAY? GOOD?

479
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:09,000
- IT'S OKAY. I'LL GET DINNER
STARTED HERE IN A SECOND.

480
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:12,666
- DINNER? NOT SO FAST, AKI.

481
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:14,125
- AREN'T YOU HUNGRY?

482
00:20:14,208 --> 00:20:16,208
YOUR MIDTERMS
ARE COMING UP SOON?

483
00:20:16,291 --> 00:20:17,666
THINK ABOUT THIS.

484
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:20,125
SHOULD YOU BE WASTING YOUR
TIME MAKING ME DINNER?

485
00:20:20,208 --> 00:20:22,000
- WELL, NO.
I GUESS I SHOULDN'T.

486
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:23,875
BUT YOU CAME ALL THIS WAY,
SO I THOUGHT...

487
00:20:23,958 --> 00:20:25,125
- YOU DIDN'T THINK.

488
00:20:25,208 --> 00:20:26,875
YOU'RE MISTAKING THE MEANS
FOR THE END AGAIN.

489
00:20:26,958 --> 00:20:29,000
THE REASON I CAME BACK
WAS TO CHECK ON YOU

490
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:30,458
AND MAKE SURE YOU WERE OKAY.

491
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:32,166
IF YOU'RE WASTING TIME ON ME,

492
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:34,500
YOU'RE PRETTY MUCH WASTING
MY TIME, AS WELL.

493
00:20:34,583 --> 00:20:36,500
ON TOP OF THAT,
I DON'T WANT YOU TO USE ME

494
00:20:36,583 --> 00:20:38,833
ME AS AN EXCUSE
WHEN YOUR GRADES SUFFER.

495
00:20:38,916 --> 00:20:41,750
YOU DON'T HAVE TO COOK FOR ME,
I'M DOING JUST FINE.

496
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:44,875
IN FACT, I'LL MAKE US DINNER
WHILE YOU STUDY.

497
00:20:44,958 --> 00:20:47,750
- HOW DOES THAT SOUND?
- SOUNDS PRETTY STUPID TO ME!

498
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:49,750
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?
ALL YOU EVER CARE ABOUT

499
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,583
ARE THOSE DUMB TEST RESULTS.

500
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:53,583
FINE. I'LL GO STUDY, THEN!

501
00:21:04,083 --> 00:21:05,708
SHE'S SO STUPID.

502
00:21:05,791 --> 00:21:07,916
I'LL MAKE SURE
I GET A GOOD GRADE.

503
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,375
THAT'LL SHUT HER UP.

504
00:21:11,958 --> 00:21:14,000
- ( clock chiming )
- OH, COME ON.

505
00:21:14,083 --> 00:21:16,250
- GOOD MORNING, YOSHII.
HOW ARE YOU?

506
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:17,583
- HEY, WHAT'S UP, AKI?

507
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:18,875
- PLEASE DON'T TALK TO ME..

508
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,458
THE STUFF I MEMORIZED AND
CRAMMED INTO MY HEAD

509
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:21,708
MIGHT COME OUT.

510
00:21:21,791 --> 00:21:24,500
- WHEN'S THE IDES OF MARCH?
- O... KAY.

511
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:27,000
GUESS WE'LL LET YOU STUDY.

512
00:21:27,083 --> 00:21:30,375
- Nishimura: ALL RIGHT. WE'RE
ABOUT TO BEGIN THE TEST. READY?

513
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:31,500
BEGIN!

514
00:21:34,291 --> 00:21:36,375
- ( reading to himself )
I CAN DO THIS. QUESTION ONE.

515
00:21:36,458 --> 00:21:41,125
334 BC! THE LAST KING OF THE
ACHAEMENID EMPIRE OF PERSIA WAS.

516
00:21:41,208 --> 00:21:42,333
ALEXANDER THE GREAT!

517
00:21:42,416 --> 00:21:44,291
NEXT!

518
00:21:44,375 --> 00:21:47,208
- I BET HE'S TAKING
THE TEST RIGHT NOW.

519
00:21:47,291 --> 00:21:49,916
WELL THEN, I SUPPOSE
I SHOULD START TOO.

520
00:21:54,125 --> 00:21:56,208
- ALL RIGHT. I DID MY BEST.

521
00:21:56,291 --> 00:21:58,458
I CAN'T BELIEVE I HAVE TIME LEFT
OVER TO DOUBLE CHECK MY ANSWERS.

522
00:21:58,541 --> 00:22:00,458
- ( clock chimes )

523
00:22:00,541 --> 00:22:02,625
- OKAY. PUT YOUR PENCILS DOWN.

524
00:22:02,708 --> 00:22:05,083
LOSERS IN THE BACK,
COLLECT THE ANSWER PAGES.

525
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,958
GOODBYE SWEET LIFE
ALL ON MY OWN.

526
00:22:19,166 --> 00:22:23,083
- REALLY? ALEXANDER THE GREAT
IS MY BROTHER.

527
00:22:23,166 --> 00:22:25,833
YOU PUT THE FIRST ANSWER WHERE
YOU SHOULD'VE PUT YOUR NAME,

528
00:22:25,916 --> 00:22:28,583
SO EVERY ANSWER
YOU PUT DOWN WAS OFF BY ONE.

529
00:22:28,666 --> 00:22:31,583
- PLEASE! DON'T CALL ME
ALEXANDER THE GREAT ANYMORE!

530
00:22:31,666 --> 00:22:33,250
- Akira: HOW ABOUT
DARIUS THE THIRD?

531
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:36,583
- WHY DO YOU ALWAYS HAVE TO
HUMILIATE ME LIKE THIS?

532
00:22:36,666 --> 00:22:38,375
I COULD'VE GOTTEN A DECENT SCORE

533
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:40,750
IF I HADN'T SCREWED THAT
SIMPLE THING UP.

534
00:22:40,833 --> 00:22:42,541
- DO YOU THINK THEY'D
FORGIVE YOU IF YOU MADE

535
00:22:42,625 --> 00:22:45,416
THE SAME MISTAKE
ON A COLLEGE ENTRANCE EXAM?

536
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:48,416
- NO. BUT I REALLY DID
TRY MY HARDEST.

537
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,000
- YOU KEEP SAYING THAT.

538
00:22:50,083 --> 00:22:53,250
REMEMBER OUR TALK ABOUT "TRYING"
BEING A MEANS TO AN END?

539
00:22:53,875 --> 00:22:55,416
- YEAH, I DO.

540
00:22:59,166 --> 00:23:01,083
SHE IS RUTHLESS.

541
00:23:01,166 --> 00:23:02,791
- ( frustrated grunt )

542
00:23:02,875 --> 00:23:04,791
- ( water dripping )

543
00:23:07,666 --> 00:23:08,875
-( tap turning on )

544
00:23:14,166 --> 00:23:16,041
- IT'S A MESS IN HERE.

545
00:23:16,125 --> 00:23:18,333
WAIT. SHE CAN'T COOK.

546
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:26,833
THESE LOOK LIKE
FAILED PAELLA DISHES.

547
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:32,416
I WONDER.

548
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:34,791
WAS SHE PRACTICING
MAKING MY FAVORITE MEAL?

549
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:40,375
- Akira: TRYING HARD
IS ONLY A MEANS TO AN END.

550
00:23:40,458 --> 00:23:42,916
IF YOU BECOME PROUD
OF THE EFFORT ITSELF,

551
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,000
YOU'RE MISTAKING
THE MEANS FOR THE END.

552
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:49,833
- FOR REAL? SHE'S SO STUPID.

553
00:23:57,083 --> 00:23:58,833
- ( theme music playing )

554
00:24:11,791 --> 00:24:14,375
( singing in Japanese )

555
00:25:29,958 --> 00:25:32,291
- Akihisa: HEY, AKIRA?
- YEAH?

556
00:25:32,375 --> 00:25:34,208
- THANKS FOR EVERYTHING.

557
00:25:34,291 --> 00:25:36,333
AND... I REALLY DO LOVE YOU.

558
00:25:36,958 --> 00:25:38,041
- YOU DO?

559
00:25:38,125 --> 00:25:39,916
- OF COURSE I DO,
BUT ONLY AS A SISTER.

560
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,250
- THAT'S SWEET,

561
00:25:41,333 --> 00:25:43,333
BUT I'M STILL NOT GOING TO
IGNORE YOUR TEST SCORE.

562
00:25:43,416 --> 00:25:45,375
- WELL, THAT SUCKS.

563
00:25:45,458 --> 00:25:47,708
- SO, AKI...
- WHAT?

564
00:25:47,791 --> 00:25:50,250
- I WAS THINKING THAT
MAYBE ONE OF THESE DAYS

565
00:25:50,333 --> 00:25:52,166
I COULD MAKE DINNER FOR YOU.

566
00:25:52,250 --> 00:25:53,500
- REALLY?

567
00:25:53,583 --> 00:25:55,916
- REALLY. BUT ONLY IF
I FEEL LIKE IT.

568
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,291
- YEAH, I GUESS THAT'S FAIR.

569
00:25:59,208 --> 00:26:00,291
- HEY, AKIRA?

570
00:26:00,375 --> 00:26:01,791
- YES, AKI.

571
00:26:01,875 --> 00:26:04,000
- DO YOU KNOW WHAT THE BEST
SPICE IN THE WORLD IS?

572
00:26:05,250 --> 00:26:08,000
- HMM. HOW SHOULD I KNOW,
I DON'T COOK.

573
00:26:08,916 --> 00:26:10,916
FINE, I GIVE UP.

574
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,791
TELL ME, WHAT IS THE BEST SPICE?

575
00:26:12,875 --> 00:26:15,875
- THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION!

576
00:26:15,958 --> 00:26:17,041
- Fukuhara: QUESTION TEN:

577
00:26:17,125 --> 00:26:19,000
NAME THE JAPANESE NOVELIST
WHO INTRODUCED

578
00:26:19,083 --> 00:26:20,541
THE "ADOLESCENT DETECTIVE GANG"

579
00:26:20,625 --> 00:26:23,000
AND THE "MYSTERY MAN OF TWENTY
FACES" TO THE WORLD.

580
00:26:23,083 --> 00:26:24,333
- Akihisa: THE THIEF
IS AMONG US!

581
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:25,541
- IT'S NOT ME.

582
00:26:25,625 --> 00:26:26,833
